arb4j (0.99.9.9.10) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  [ Stephen Crowley ]
  * MuntzPadeFunction is a ComplexFunctional<Complex,Complex,ComplexFunction>:
    v becomes the input parameter to evaluate, not a mutable field.
    RiccatiMittagLefflerFunction extends MuntzPadeFunction; v field and
    muntzCoefficientsAtV are gone. The curried Muntz coefficient sequence
    a:k➔v➔a_k(v) is built once in the Context using a forward-declared
    mutually-recursive cluster (a, S) so the integer memo on k fires at
    every v without recompilation. New top-level MuntzPadeApproximantAtV
    holds the per-v Pade pair built lazily inside evaluate.
  * Issue #994: Re-entrancy guard on Expression.compile() ends the
    recompile cascade in mutually-recursive curried sequence clusters.
    A peer's generateFunctionInitializer at line 2609 forced
    nestedExpression.compile() when variablesDeclared was false; for
    a ⇔ S where each references the other through a curried
    ComplexFunctionSequence (k➔v➔body), this re-entered compile()
    on an Expression whose generateFunctionalElement had already
    consumed its placeholderVariable, producing an inner functional
    Expression with independentVariable=null and crashing splice with
    UndefinedReference 'v'. compileInProgress flag short-circuits the
    re-entrant call; the outer compile's symbolic class-name reference
    in bytecode is resolved at JVM-load time when the recursive
    compile chain has finished. Test
    SelfRecursiveCurriedSequenceTest covers self-recursive and
    mutually-recursive curried sequence cases.
  * Universal lazy ∂/∂v on every Expression-compiled Function. Function
    grows derivative(VariableReference) and derivative(String) defaults;
    Expression.derivative(VariableReference) does pure-Java AST surgery
    via deepCloneExpression + rootNode.differentiate(probe).simplify
    with no source re-parsing; every generated class now emits
    getExpression() returning a back-pointer field populated at
    instantiate() time so the default reaches the source AST. Per-name
    partialDerivativeCache memoizes compiled partials.
  * Function gains a Jacobian class and jacobian(String[]/
    VariableReference[]/VariableNode[]) defaults. Jacobian carries a
    Unicode toString() while typeset() stays LaTeX.
  * Extract MuntzPadeFunction; RiccatiMittagLefflerFunction extends it,
    implements ComplexFunction, and derives evaluation order from bits.
    Fluent shape on padePolynomials, muntzCoefficientsAtV, solveHankel.
    Cache lifecycle split: clearCache drops references, disposeCache
    closes native; invalidateCache override drops the Padé cache and
    α-vector.
  * partialDerivativeWithRespectToV rewritten to use p.derivative("v"),
    q.derivative("v"), r.derivative("v") directly, registered under
    p_dv, q_dv, r_dv on the shared Context so the bytecode field
    descriptors L<name>; resolve to the actual loaded classes on the
    shared ExpressionClassLoader. JacobianAtVTest green at all three
    closed-form pins (w₁=1/Γ(1.6), w₂=1.5/Γ(2.2), w₃=1.25/Γ(2.8)); full
    suite 780/780 in ~8s.
  * Confine fat-jar shading to the -Pdebian profile so the development
    build is unaffected.
  * Bundle JavaFX inside the shaded fat jar; strip --add-opens javafx.*
    flags from installed wrappers; add arb.applications.Launcher to
    bypass the OpenJFX classpath-launch guard.
  * Rewrite ch.qos.logback class names inside the fat jar's logback*.xml
    after shade so logging configuration tracks the relocated packages.
  * Headless-JavaFX support: bin/xvfbrun, bin/snapshot, ScreenshotDriver.
  * arbshell wrapper: forward classpath to jshell driver and remote
    agent; strip jshell -R-prefixed JPMS flags.
  * Javadoc: skip by default (opt in with -Djavadoc.skip=false), make
    failures non-fatal, switch to <subpackages>, exclude arb.solvers.
  * Gaussian-process sampler: runtime sample-length control bar; default
    range 0..2000; restore StationaryGaussianProcessSampler to commit
    6594908; restore per-row progress meter to System.out; drop FFT
    cross-check overlays from sampler chart build.
  * Drop the Known Test Failures section from README.
  * Strip apostrophes from comments inside install-bin.sh awk block.
  * Riemann–Liouville fractional integral I^μ as a first-class symbolic
    operator. New RiemannLiouvilleFractionalIntegralNode mirrors the
    Caputo derivative node: parser keyword fracint, full AST surgery
    semantics (accept, dependsOn, differentiate, integral=I^(μ+1),
    spliceInto, type, typeset LaTeX, toString Unicode), and a generic
    integrand-based bytecode generation path. Closed-form short-circuit
    overrides on VariableNode, ExponentiationNode (t^β →
    Γ(β+1)/Γ(β+μ+1)·t^(β+μ)), AdditionNode, NegationNode,
    MultiplicationNode (constant·f), DivisionNode (f/constant),
    LiteralConstantNode (c·t^μ/Γ(μ+1)), FunctionNode (inline body),
    and the Riemann–Liouville node itself (semigroup
    I^μ∘I^ν = I^(μ+ν)).
  * Inverse identity D^μ[I^μ f] = f verified at non-integer μ on
    multiple test functions at 256 bits. Volterra residual test on a
    Müntz partial sum (qrh.tex Test 1) shows the first non-vanishing
    coefficient at t^((N+1)μ) equals −a_{N+1}(v).
  * Wrapper RiemannLiouvilleFractionalIntegralNode exposes its
    closedFormResult through hasClosedFormFractionalDerivative and
    fractionalDerivative so the closed-form path is reachable from the
    parent Caputo node.
  * ConstantCoefficientFractionalRiccatiEquation reduced to a
    deprecated stub that redirects to RiccatiMittagLefflerFunction.
  * Expression.context encapsulated: field is now private with a
    getContext()/setContext() pair (getContext lazy-constructs a
    Context if absent), the bytecode-emitted context field on
    generated classes carries ACC_PROTECTED, and Context.setFieldValue
    falls back to getDeclaredField+setAccessible to remain reflective
    against the tightened access. All in-tree callers migrated to
    getContext() across 11 files.
  * Parser arrow normalization widened: ➜, ↦, ⟶, ⟼ all fold to ➔ at
    the lexer stage so all arrow variants parse identically.
  * Generic Jacobian class on the Function interface (#991): the
    jacobian(String[])/jacobian(VariableReference[])/jacobian(
    VariableNode[]) defaults on Function build a Jacobian<D,R,F>
    instance whose closure under self-application yields Hessians for
    free; closes #991 Phase 1.
  * Closes: #984, #991. Test suite 786/786 green.
  * Expression.shouldCache enables peek/poke memoization for generated
    functionals (#993). The !isGeneratedFunctional() clause is dropped
    so integer-domain sequences whose codomain is a function type now
    receive the integer-keyed TreeMap memo. generateCachePeek and
    generateCachePokeEpilogue gain functional-codomain branches: peek
    returns the cached function reference directly (no result.set, no
    out-parameter aliasing); poke dups the function instance left on
    the stack by generateFunctionalElement, pokes it under k, and
    returns it (no <init>, no set). Function references are immutable
    handles, so the deep-copy-on-hit dance used for value-type
    codomains is skipped. The Müntz–Padé recurrence
    a:k➔v➔…·a(k-1)(v)+r(v)·S(k)(v),
    S:k➔v➔sum(j➔a(j)(v)·a(k-1-j)(v){j=1..k-2}) drops from O(M³) to
    O(M²) per v.
  * MuntzPadeFunction.solveHankel: Padé numerator built from the
    compiled functional n➔a(n)+sum(j➔q[j]·a(n-j){j=1..n-1}) (#990
    step 3 redo with the q[j] component-access bracket form);
    DiagonalPade encapsulates the (P,Q) pair and its sub-Context
    lifecycle (#990 step 2); HankelSystem extracts the Hankel
    coefficient linear solve into arb.solvers (#990 step 1); dead
    pz/qz scratch dropped from evaluatePadeAtCachedOrder (#990 step
    4); try-with-resources on H, neg_b, qMat in solveHankel.
  * Closes: #990, #993. Test suite 790/790 green on JDK 26.

 -- Stephen Crowley <stephencrowley214@gmail.com>  Wed, 29 Apr 2026 02:55:00 -0500

arb4j (0.99.9.9.9) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  [ Stephen Crowley ]
  * New upstream milestone 0.99.9.9.9: parallel Real.autocorrelation
    over lag strides backed by a ThreadLocal scalar pair, bidirectional
    Wiener–Khinchin cross-checks (IDFT of empirical PSD on the
    covariance chart, DFT of empirical autocorrelation on the PSD
    chart), Recalculate button driving both panels in lockstep, and
    JavaFX 26 / JDK 26 build target.
  * Switch JDK build-dependency and runtime dependency from openjdk-25
    to openjdk-26 (control, rules JAVA_HOME path).
  * Install every script under bin/ to /usr/bin via debian/arb4j.install.
  * Drop empty override_dh_install in debian/rules so the
    arb4j.install manifest is actually honoured (previously the empty
    override silently disabled dh_install and bin/ shipped nothing).
  * Relocate every bin/ wrapper to a real FHS layout. /usr/share/arb4j
    holds env.sh, class.path, pom.xml, version, shell.start, and a
    lib/ tree containing every transitive Maven dependency JAR. Each
    /usr/bin wrapper sources env.sh and reads ARB4J_HOME, ARB4J_JAR,
    ARB4J_NATIVE_DIR, ARB4J_CLASSPATH instead of computing BASEDIR
    from $0. The dev-only updateClasspath script (which calls mvn
    against a checkout) is no longer installed; arb4jVersion is
    rewritten to cat /usr/share/arb4j/version.
  * debian/env.sh.in, debian/install-bin.sh: new helpers driving the
    rewrite. install-bin.sh uses awk to redirect BASEDIR= and FMDIR=
    lines, replace `cat $BASEDIR/class.path` with $ARB4J_CLASSPATH,
    redirect -Djava.library.path and LD_LIBRARY_PATH to
    $ARB4J_NATIVE_DIR, drop dev-only $BASEDIR/build/classes from
    classpaths, and resolve sibling wrapper invocations through PATH.
  * Ship a single shaded fat jar at /usr/share/java/arb4j.jar with
    every transitive Maven dependency relocated under
    org.arblib.shaded.* (asm, slf4j, logback, snakeyaml, fair_acc
    chartfx/dataset/math/bench, jlatexmath, vineflower, graphvizjava,
    j2v8, svgsalamander, ikonli, controlsfx, commons, hdrhistogram,
    jtransforms, jlargearrays, intellij/jetbrains/jsr305 annotations,
    nashornpromise, pngj, junit, hamcrest). JavaFX is excluded from
    the shade and supplied by the runtime JDK. Drop the
    /usr/share/arb4j/lib/ tree and the /usr/share/arb4j/class.path
    file; ARB4J_CLASSPATH now equals ARB4J_JAR.

